METRIC_BROWSER_HELP: The Context table below shows the most recently computed rollup of KPIs for different network characteristics represented by the most left columns (ex. SNSSAI or TAC). You can refine the table results using the filters panel. You can interact with the table by selecting or right-clicking a row. When a row is selected you can view Historical Data about the row selection or view Other Contexts which can be opened using the characteristic identifiers in the row. Hover over a cell to see the collection time.
ARIA_CLEAR_FILTERS_DESCRIPTION: Clear all selected filters for the table
AUTOREFRESH_TOOLTIP: You can turn this off in the table settings
FILTER_HELP: You can add new filters using the 'Add' button. Once filters are applied you can select, deselect, edit, or remove them. Filters you configure will be persisted in this browser on your computer for your next visit. If you close the Context tab you will lose your configurations. Your filters will not be available in incognito mode.
